(51, 'What is economics', '<p>The central idea of economics is that people make choices with scarce resources, and they interact with other people when they make these choices. In Principles of Economics, you will be exposed to all of economics at a basic level. You will be introduced to microeconomics, learning how producers and consumers interact in markets, and learn about concepts important in economic decision making, such as opportunity cost.</p>', 'assets/course_videos/696e73742d314f31385f2432382d746b3330303835353536.mp4', 'assets/playlist_thumbnail/696e73742d314f31385f2432382d746b3330303835353536.jpg', 1, 28, '2019-01-31 08:59:22', NULL, NULL, '00:02:55', 1, NULL, 1),
(52, 'Why Study Economics', '<p>Because&nbsp;<strong>economics</strong>&nbsp;provides a rigorous way of thinking about trade-offs, incentives, and costs and benefits, it has many real-world applications. ...<strong>Economics</strong>&nbsp;can help us understand how people make financial decisions and how simple changes can result in better outcomes.&nbsp;<strong>Economics</strong>&nbsp;is <strong>important</strong>&nbsp;you get to know how societies, governments, businesses, households, and individuals allocate their scarce resources. The economics&nbsp;can also provide valuable knowledge for making decisions in everyday life.&nbsp;<strong>Economics</strong>&nbsp;is concerned with the optimal distribution of resources in society.</p>', 'assets/course_videos/696e73742d314f31385f2432382d746b3330303930303338.mp4', 'assets/playlist_thumbnail/696e73742d314f31385f2432382d746b3330303930303338.jpg', 1, 28, '2019-01-31 09:02:30', NULL, NULL, '00:01:38', 2, NULL, 1),
(53, 'Difference between Economics and Finance', '<p>The&nbsp;<strong>difference between finance</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>economics</strong>. Although they are often taught and presented as separate disciplines,&nbsp;<strong>economics and finance</strong>&nbsp;are interrelated and inform and influence each other. Investors care about these studies because they also influence the markets to a great degree. Although they are often taught and presented as separate disciplines,&nbsp;<em>economics and finance</em>&nbsp;are interrelated and inform and influence each other. Investors care about these studies because they also influence the markets to a great degree.</p>', 'assets/course_videos/696e73742d314f31385f2432382d746b3330303930343333.mp4', 'assets/playlist_thumbnail/696e73742d314f31385f2432382d746b3330303930343333.jpg', 1, 28, '2019-01-31 09:09:44', NULL, NULL, '00:01:55', 3, NULL, 1),
(54, 'Law of Demand - Overview and Exceptions', '<p>The&nbsp;<strong>law of demand</strong>&nbsp;states that quantity purchased varies inversely with price. In other words, the higher the price, the lower the quantity demanded. This phenomenon occurs because when consumers&#39; opportunity cost increases, they must give something else up or switch to a substitute product.This phenomenon occurs because when consumers&#39; opportunity cost increases, they must give something else up or switch to a substitute product.</p><p><strong>Supply and Demand:</strong></p><ul><li>P &ndash; price</li><li>Q &ndash; quantity of goods</li><li>S &ndash; supply</li><li>D &ndash; demand</li></ul><p><strong>The four basic laws of supply and demand are:</strong></p><ol><li>If demand increases and supply remains unchanged, then it leads to higher equilibrium price and higher quantity.</li><li>If demand decreases and supply remains unchanged, then it leads to lower equilibrium price and lower quantity.</li><li>If supply increases and demand remains unchanged, then it leads to lower equilibrium price and higher quantity.</li><li>If supply decreases and demand remains unchanged, then it leads to higher equilibrium price and lower quantity.</li></ol>', 'assets/course_videos/696e73742d314f31385f2432382d746b3330303931323035.mp4', 'assets/playlist_thumbnail/696e73742d314f31385f2432382d746b3330303931323035.jpg', 1, 28, '2019-01-31 09:13:59', NULL, NULL, '00:02:20', 4, NULL, 1),
(55, 'Basic Management Skills for Beginners', '<p>There are four basic management skills anyone must master to have any&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.thebalancecareers.com/getting-a-first-management-job-2275109\">success in a management job</a>. These four basic skills are to&nbsp;<strong>plan, organize, direct, and control</strong>&nbsp;and are discussed separately in detail below.</p><p>Plan</p><p><a href=\"https://www.thebalancecareers.com/how-to-manage-2275297\">Planning</a>&nbsp;is the first and most important step in any management task. It also is the most often overlooked or purposely skipped a step. While the amount of planning and the detail required will vary from task to task, to skip this task is to invite sure disaster except by blind luck. That&#39;s what gives us the adage of the 6 P&#39;s of planning (or 7 P&#39;s depending on how you count).</p>', 'assets/course_videos/696e73742d314f31385f2432392d746b3330303932333535.mp4', 'assets/playlist_thumbnail/696e73742d314f31385f2432392d746b3330303932333535.jpg', 1, 29, '2019-01-31 09:24:48', NULL, NULL, '00:01:30', 1, NULL, 1),
(56, 'Inventory Basics - Inventory Management', '<p>This is a detailed guide to getting started. We make the assumption that you&rsquo;re starting from scratch, with only a vague system for tracking your inventory. You may not have part numbers, named locations, or the most basic attributes of a simple inventory system. (You may not have any inventory system in place at all!) Even if you never use our software, we hope that you&rsquo;ll find this guide helpful for setting up an inventory system that gets the job done.</p><p><strong>The Critical Elements of a Pretty Good Inventory System</strong></p><ul><li><em>done</em>Well Organized Location Names</li><li><em>done</em>Location Labels that are easy to read, and unambiguous</li><li><em>done</em>Unique, Short, and Unmistakable Item Numbers</li><li><em>done</em>Units of Measure</li><li><em>done</em>A Good Starting Count</li><li><em>done</em>Software that tracks all inventory activity</li><li><em>done</em>Good Policies</li><li><em>done</em>Most Important: People who know and follow good policies</li></ul>', 'assets/course_videos/696e73742d314f31385f2432392d746b3330303932353339.mp4', 'assets/playlist_thumbnail/696e73742d314f31385f2432392d746b3330303932353339.jpg', 1, 29, '2019-01-31 09:34:18', NULL, NULL, '00:02:28', 2, NULL, 1),
(57, 'What is Business Management?', '<p>The field of business management or business administration encompasses all aspect of operating an organization. This includes strategic planning, resource management, IT management, workforce development, financial management and much more. A large organization can have multiple layers of management from a board of directors all the way down to a branch or division manager. Managers are responsible for strategic decision making and the growth and success of the organization. To excel in business management, individuals must have outstanding leadership, creative thinking, problem solving and communication skills.</p>', 'assets/course_videos/696e73742d314f31385f2433302d746b3330303935383133.mp4', 'assets/playlist_thumbnail/696e73742d314f31385f2433302d746b3330303935383133.jpg', 1, 30, '2019-01-31 10:10:13', NULL, NULL, '00:01:30', 1, NULL, 1),
(58, 'Introduction to Quality Management System', '<p>In most modern organisations, it is inevitable to link their unique management style with a formalised and structured management system.&nbsp; As globalisation propagates, common expectations in business and communications directs us towards the vastly popular Quality Management System - ISO 9001:2015. This system enables management to continually monitor and manage quality within the organisation eventually paving the way for continuous improvement and increased customer satisfaction.</p><p><strong>Objective</strong><br />To provide participants with a basic understanding on the rationale of implementing a structured management system within an organisation. To enable participants to understand the expectations of the requirements of the new standards and terminology.</p>', 'assets/course_videos/696e73742d314f31385f2433302d746b3330313031333034.mp4', 'assets/playlist_thumbnail/696e73742d314f31385f2433302d746b3330313031333034.jpg', 1, 30, '2019-01-31 10:20:50', NULL, NULL, '00:00:53', 2, NULL, 1),
(59, 'Operations Management: Definition, Principles,  Trends', '<p><em>Operations management</em>&nbsp;is the administration of business practices aimed at ensuring maximum efficiency within a business, which in turn helps to improve profitability.</p><p>Operations management is the business function that responsible to&nbsp;<strong>planning</strong>,<strong>organizing</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>coordinating</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>controlling</strong>&nbsp;the resources needed to produce a company&#39;s products and services.</p><p>Ultimately, the way that an organization carries out&nbsp;<strong>operations management</strong>depends upon the nature of products or services that it offers. ... Some of the most prominent&nbsp;<strong>examples of operations management</strong>&nbsp;in health care include controlling costs and improving the quality of service provided to patients.</p>', 'assets/course_videos/696e73742d314f31385f2433302d746b3330313032393432.mp4', 'assets/playlist_thumbnail/696e73742d314f31385f2433302d746b3330313032393432.jpg', 1, 30, '2019-01-31 10:32:08', NULL, NULL, '00:02:19', 3, NULL, 1),
